genresAdvancedInfo.name: dutch experimental electronic
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This subgenre of Dutch experimental music focuses specifically on electronic sounds and production techniques. It often involves the use of synthesizers, samplers, and other electronic instruments to create complex and layered soundscapes. Dutch experimental electronic music can be both abstract and danceable, and it frequently incorporates elements of techno, ambient, and other electronic genres.
